Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice (see pantry for amount) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Kiwi Salsa ==

Meanwhile, peel the @Kiwi{1}, then cut into 1cm chunks. Halve the @Red Chilli{1} lengthways, deseed, then finely chop.

Zest and halve the @Lime{1}.

Pop the kiwi and chilli (add less if you'd prefer things milder) into a #medium bowl{}. Squeeze in half the lime juice, then add the @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the salsa (see pantry for both amounts). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together, then set aside.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Charred Corn ==

Drain the @Sweetcorn{160%g} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%mins}. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Transfer the charred corn to a #bowl{}. Set aside.

== Caribbean Style Double Prawns ==

Meanwhile, drain the @King Prawns{300%g}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Wipe out the (now empty) #frying pan{}, then put back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the prawns, @Caribbean Style Jerk{1%sachet} and garlic. Stir-fry for ~{2-3%mins}.

Add the charred corn, @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount) to the prawns.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat slightly and simmer for ~{3-4%mins}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Remove the pan from the heat. Stir in the @Mango Chutney{40%g} and @Butter{20%g} (see pantry for amount) until melted. Add a splash of water if the sauce is a little too thick.

== To Serve ==

Share the rice between #bowls{}.

Spoon over the Caribbean style prawns, spooning over any remaining sauce from the pan.

Serve the kiwi salsa alongside. Sprinkle with the lime zest to finish.

Enjoy!